Brendan Rodgers was ordered to pay £400 and £375 costs at Blackburn magistrates' court for leaving a £69,950 terrace house in Accrington .
Rodgers and business partner Judith O'Hagan were found guilty of ignoring an improvement notice issued by Hyndburn Council .
The house is undergoing a £13million regeneration project to sort out over 200 derelict empty properties .